-- Scandi Standard aims for listing this summer - report
-- 
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 02:01AM EDT
-- None



STOCKHOLM, April 3 (Reuters) - Scandi Standard, owner of chicken producer Kronfagel Holding, is to be listed on the Stockholm stock exchange this summer, business daily Dagens Industri said on Thursday, quoting sources.

Kronfagel, with operations in Sweden and Denmark, has a turnover of around 5.4 billion Swedish crowns ($833 million). Investment bank Carnegie and Danske Bank have been picked as advisors, Dagens Industri said.